label dream_one:

    "In her dreams, she is young again. "

    "Her face is red, her eyes are puffy, and her nose is clogged with snot. The last of a long series of unsuccessful spellcasting forays had worn her composure down until it snapped clean in half." 

    "In a moment of childish fury and frustration, she had burst into tears, stamping around and flinging her book from its place on the table." 

    "Despite her tutor's best efforts, her temper burned as bright and fiery as ever."

    "Exasperated by her outburst, her mother had confined her to her room, where she would remain for the rest of the night."

    "She blinks, and suddenly her brother, Jingshen, sits behind her."

    "In his hand he holds a brush that gently untangles dark black strands until the comb can travel all the way down her luscious locks without interruption."

    "He tells her it will rejuvenate her magical abilities, that an affinity for witchcraft requires a corresponding cosmetic upkeep, but she knows the truth."

    "Children, when asked to conjure up an image of their mother, would first begin with softness."

    "Fingers carding through unruly strands, featherlight kisses to the temple, a warm embrace." 

    "In the Yue family household, tenderness was only permitted in combination with worship, and Jun's mother bowed to no one." 

    "Perhaps, in her own way, she was doing what she thought was best for them."

    "Like any mother, she wished to impart important lessons to her next of kin."

    "In her eyes, there was nothing more crucial to learn than ruthlessness."

    "But Jun was never good at conforming herself to instruction without sufficient drive. She had too much pride in herself to believe anyone else knew better than her. Who else would hold her head high but she?"

    "So maybe this, in its own way, was their little act of rebellion. Letting their words fall out dull and unsharpened. Raising their hands not to hurt, but to hold."

    "Promises whispered into the nighttime breeze."

    "In this quiet moment, she was safe."

    "She was loved."

    "Unconditionally, selflessly, wholly."

    "She opens her mouth to ask a question she already knows the answer to."

    "{i}We'll always be together, won't we?{/i}"

    "."
    "."
    "."

    "In her dreams, she is young again."

    "She is smart, she is powerful, she is bold."

    "Her brother learns faster, works harder, and what he lacks in firmness, he makes up for in physical prowess."

    "He is well-liked and well treated. He is the golden boy, the bright-eyed shepherd's dog herding the black sheep back into the shadows."

    "What warmth could she find in his praise, in his adoration?"

    "Standing next to him, she could hardly be seen."

    "…"

    "Vampires don't do well in the sun."

    "He is scorching hot to the touch, and so brilliant is his radiance that he shines light on things she has never seen before."

    "A smile from their mother. A glimmer of love so full of promise that she couldn't look away. "

    "A harsh reminder of the affection she did everything possible to cohere herself to."

    "Fangs sinking deep into flesh, draining fresh blood from helpless bodies. "

    "She suckles on the skin and imagines herself infant and innocent. "

    "Dumb, pliant, and perfect. A baby clinging to its mother's breast."

    "Untainted, unmarred." 

    "Did her mother cradle her then? Did she sing sweet melodies as she rocked her to sleep?"

    "Was she everything and anything she could have ever wanted?"

    "The stars in the sky, the missing piece which made it all make sense?"

    "Made it all right?"

    "She throws herself into her studies. She doesn't stop until she's top of her class." 

    "She spends sleepless days practicing every spell any dusty tome could give her. She doesn't rest until she can cast them all as easily as breathing."

    "{i}Look at me.{/i}"

    "She talks herself up to anyone who will hear it. She's never wrong, she never falters. She does not bend to accommodate anyone. If people are put off by her, that's their problem, not hers."

    "She is cold and calculating. Every action she takes is a measured step to climb higher, to grab more power."

    "She is cruel and vindictive, but logically sound. She has her goals and is willing to fight for them."

    "She looks in the mirror and sees her mother's face: harsh lines and an icy stare."

    "Look at me."

    "Look at me."

    "LOOK AT ME!"

