    "…"

    "When her brother becomes the heir, it's the most logical conclusion. He's older and wiser, kind and well-mannered." 

    "He's the man."

    "Jun's gaze has grown more discerning over the years. "

    "Jingshen is cowardly. He does what he is told to gain approval. He is quiet and prefers to be a recluse, disinterested in the company of others unless forced to."

    "He panics under pressure, and worst of all"

    "he is afraid of blood." 

    "How can he rule with an iron fist? How can he call himself a vampire when he can't bring himself to kill like one?"

    "To feed like one?"

    "It should've been her."

    "She would be everything that disappointment, that failure, could never be. She would have the balls that were wasted on him."

    "She takes on a new identity in the privacy of her room, a person that her mother would love, if only she could accept."

    "Fine silk tops, imposing cloaks, dapper suits. She is a prince in her own right."

    "She parts her hair just so, and finds she does not know where Jingshen ends and Jun begins."

    "Outside, she has the beauty of a fair maiden. She preens under the attention pretty dresses and practiced poise can bring. "

    "Her expression of femininity is so flamboyant it becomes a performance. "

    "But she can never be subservient and submissive to their whims. She is too argumentative and brash. Too noisy."

    "She wants to be the man she never can be while holding onto the woman she is. "

    "A frankensteined masterpiece of son and daughter, boy and girl. They hold hands and play ring around the rosie while fire meets flesh and bone."

    "Still, she"

    "he"

    "{i}they{/i}"

    "try."

    "Shoving this malformed creation towards an ivory tower, a picturesque pedestal."

    "Can you see me now, mother? Have you found me?"

    "Because I could never lose you."

    "I find traces of you everywhere. In me, in the half-assed mimicries of love and desire I cannot parse."

    "In men, in women. "

    "Day or night, rain or shine. I am right there beside you, nipping at your heels, doggedly pursuing."

    "Mommy, I love you."

    "Don't you love me, too?"

    "Can't you hear me screaming your name?"

    "Mommy, mommy-"

    "{i}I love you.{/i}"

