label dream_two:

    "In her dreams, she sees Astrid. "

    "Not the Astrid that keeps her under lock and key, shrinking her world until all that is in it is iron and rust and blood and her, standing vigilant, tall, and unmoving. "

    "No. This Astrid is.. sweeter. She doesn't gnash her teeth or spit venom. "

    "And maybe she's more dog than anything else, because she is soft, downy fur and peppered kisses." 

    "Like man's best friend, she nuzzles into her shoulder, pulling her close to her chest. She expects and wants for nothing except the warmth of another. "

    "With her, Jun doesn't have to be anything. Daughter, sister, noble.. all these fall away and lay her bare. Naked and vulnerable."

    "She braces for a hurt that doesn't come. Where it would be so easy to strike, she is met with gentleness."

    "As Astrid presses another kiss to her temple, humming a soothing tune she can't quite place.. she thinks, oddly enough, of her mother."

    "."
    "."
    "."

    "Then Astrid's face distorts above her. Her expression is lost in the haze. "

    "The affection, however, is not so easy to stamp out."

    "It survives in half-baked fantasies, circling over her head like a vulture. They play behind her eyes, scenes for her to examine behind closed doors. The ache settles into the hollow between her neck and shoulder."

    "Living together in a quaint little cabin. Astrid's hunting and foraging expertise means they don't have to struggle to get by. "

    "Jun wraps her arms around Astrid's waist and rests her head on her shoulder as the scent of their soon to be dinner wafts through the kitchen."

    "She runs Astrid a bath and smooths her thumb over every scar. For once, she doesn't have to be on guard. She can indulge in her wants beyond fending for her life. She chooses Jun every time."

    "Her laughter rings out like church bells as Jun tells her another ridiculous anecdote. Her cheeks are tinted in the prettiest shade of red."

    "Jun calls her name from a distance. Astrid's tail wags uncontrollably as she turns around to greet her."

    "In these brief snapshots, the girl by her side is unrecognizable. She is constructed of the fiction Jun is forced to write based on what little inspiration reality provides her."

    "As her hunger bleeds into the physical world, her palate grows more refined. Iron on her tongue and the shadow of someone she yearns to know burned into the ground. Someone who she will never meet for as long as she is kept in this prison."

    "Rather than drive herself mad with what-ifs and delusions of some far flung future, she tempers her expectations."

    "Astrid is putty in her hands, a moldable clay changing shape to fit her needs."

    "She doesn't want fairytale endings and rainbows she won't see the end of. "

    "She needs to be logical. Realistic."

    "The love she knows would never be this delicate."

    "She tries again."

    "."
    "."
    "."

    "Astrid responds in kind to her provocations. She is rough and mean, all sharp edges and teeth sinking in. "

    "They rip into one another like wild animals. Jun licks the blood off of Astrid's teeth. Astrid's hands wrap around her throat."

    "She savors these vignettes of violence. They are, to her, the kindest thing. "

    "Jun isn't a lawfully wedded wife or a girl next door. The affection people like her deserve isn't picket fences and pinky promises." 

    "This is something she can deal with. She is no stranger to these types of arrangements."

    "Astrid isn't fluent in matters of the heart, so they can both settle for the next best thing."

    "Bodies are more practical with their needs. "

    "Skin on skin, roving touches, lecherous gazes."

    "Sinking in and taking."

    "The heat rises to a boiling point. Jun's heart thrums in her chest."

    "If Astrid reaches deep enough inside of her, will it be love?"

    "Yes, this will do just fine."
